Pour the @water{300%ml} into a #medium saucepan{} with a #tight-fitting lid{}. Stir in the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp}, cover with the lid and bring to the boil on medium-high heat. Once boiling, turn the heat down to its lowest setting. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

While the rice cooks, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. When the oil is hot, add the @British Beef Mince{360%g} and cook until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. Use a #wooden spoon{} to break it up as it cooks. Drain and discard any excess fat from the beef, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Meanwhile, halve the @Bell Pepper{2} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into small pieces. Trim the @Carrot{2} then quarter lengthways (no need to peel). Chop widthways into small pieces.

Stir the @Mexican Style Spice Mix{1%packet} into the mince along with the chopped veggies. Cook, stirring, until the veggies start to soften, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Then, pour in the @Water for the Beef{100%ml}, @Chopped Tomatoes with Onion and Garlic{1%can}, @Tomato Passata{1%jar} and @Red Wine Stock Paste{28%g}. Stir and bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until the mixture is thick and mince and veg are cooked, ~{15-20%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, zest the @Lime{1} then chop into wedges. Pop the @Soured Cream{150%g} in a #bowl{} and stir in the lime zest. Season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{}.

When ready to serve, fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and divide between bowls. Season the beef chilli with salt and pepper if needed. Reserve 2 portions of the chilli - this is for your lunch burrito. Serve the remaining chilli on top of the rice and finish with a dollop of zesty soured cream (reserve half for your burritos) and the lime wedges for squeezing over. Dinner is served. Enjoy!

== Lunch Burrito ==

When you're ready to pack lunch, drain the @Sweetcorn{150%g} in a #sieve{}. Then stir it into the reserved chilli. Grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{30%g}.

Lay the @Super Soft Tortillas with Whole Wheat{4} onto a #board{} and spread with the reserved soured cream. Top with the @Wild Rocket{20%g}, the chilli and then the cheese. Tuck in the ends and roll into a burrito. Wrap in #foil{} and refrigerate. Enjoy cold, or alternatively heat up in a #microwave{} until piping hot.

> TIP: Roll your burrito just before eating for maximum freshness. Enjoy!